body:
@gorgos The solution was bumping the `gas` value in `buidler.config.js`. E.g.

```javascript
module.exports = {
  networks: {
    buidlerevm: {
      gas: 12000000,
      blockGasLimit: 0x1fffffffffffff,
      allowUnlimitedContractSize: true,
      timeout: 1800000
    }
  }
};

```

@kendricktan's solution works, but there are some nuances:

+ If "gas" is set to "auto", Hardhat fails to correctly calculate the amount of gas required to deploy a contract that deploys other contract(s).
+ If "gas" is hardcoded to a very high value, it works.

// solidity: "0.8.0",
  solidity: {
    version: "0.8.0",
    settings: {
      optimizer: {
        enabled: true,
        runs: 200
      }
    }
  },
i simply added this to hardhat config . problem solved. optimizer enable true and runs 200

fwiw, just this worked for me
```
  networks: {
    hardhat: {
      allowUnlimitedContractSize: true
    }
  },
```

networks: {
    hardhat: {
      allowUnlimitedContractSize: true
    }
  }, 

this also works as well as just enable run on 1 not 200 will do trick for few as well

Just enable the optimizer in hardhat.config.js

```
solidity: {
    version: "0.7.5",
    settings: {
      optimizer: {
        enabled: true,
        runs: 200
      }
    }
  },
```
